    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-09T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-09T07:00:00-05:00" n="757"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.115/112: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Barcelona</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-09T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 9, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram of October 8, 8 p.m. Councilor of Economy expressed surprise last
                    night at news of proposed cotton seizure and asked for <pb facs="0834" n="735"
                        xml:id="pg_735"/> original communication of labor organization to
                    International Banking Corporation in order to lay matter before a meeting of
                    Council today. He promised to notify Consulate General and International Banking
                    Corporation of result of meeting. Embassy at Madrid informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
